reviews.review: There are wonderful actions scenes and the movie is fast paced. There are some scarier moments (I wouldnt recommend this for children under 8). Also there are just Moments that make you cringe. The first 3/4 of the film are great, the ending is almost confusing.
Great storyline and a feelgood ending.

Felt rushed like two movies crammed into one. A very unfulfilling end that mostly felt like a repeat of other movies. Could have been so much more.

Way to much exposition instead of storytelling.  Felt like watching an episode of TV after missing a few episodes, like you missed a piece of the story no one is talking about anymore.  

Dialog was very cringe in a lot of spots, humour was forced and un-funny, and you can see the cinematography was very cut and paste from other Star Wars movies.
Over plotted and underdeveloped, but darn fun to watch. The broad strokes were well done, each actor gets a moment to shine
what a big fat goofy mess

Honestly the final entry pulled itself together better than I could have anticipated considering it's divergent predecessor. I enjoyed the character development and plot choices Abrams made to wrap everything up and left only wishing he would have had creative control over all 3 to make a truly great trilogy. Sure there are some corny moments and cringe worthy lines, but what Star Wars movie doesn't have those? I believe there are far more moments that any fan's emotions will be elicited for the better. That being said the originals are still far suppieor, but I believe time will show 7,8,9 > 1,2,3 with 5 still at the top.

This movie is getting a lot of hate online, but I found it to be much better than the last one. For what it is, and what JJ had to work with, it turned out to be much better than expected. It's not great, but at least it's an average entertaining Start Wars film, and that's good enough for the conclusion.
